## <a id="2-7-3"></a> v2.7.3

**Release Date: January 6, 2020**

### Features

New features and changes in this release:

* The beta <%= vars.single_leader_plan %> service plan in <%= vars.product_full %> now supports failing over to a follower in
  a different data center. 
  <%= partial '../../p-mysql/partials/mysql/multi_site_beta' %>
* Operators are able to monitor MySQL metrics on the Healthwatch Indicator Protocol dashboard. For more information, see [Indicator Protocol Dashboard (Beta)](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/healthwatch/indicator-protocol.html).
* Updated HA Clusters to only retain 3 days of binary logs, which minimizes persistent disk usage. 

### Security Fixes

This release includes the following security fix:

* Updates Envoy to v1.12.2, which fixes CVE-2019-18801, CVE-2019-18802, and CVE-2019-18838.
* Updates Percona Server to v5.7.28-31, which fixes several CVEs. For more information, see [here](https://usn.ubuntu.com/4070-1/) and [here](https://usn.ubuntu.com/4195-1/).
* Bumped Golang to v1.13.x, which fixes several CVEs.

### Resolved Issues

This release has the following fixes:

* Single node service instances no longer emit irrelevant Leader-Follower metrics.
* Fixed smoke tests error output to explain the actual error rather than a confusing BOSH-related error.
* Moved audit logs to be stored on persistent disk, instead of the syslog endpoint.

