## <a id="2-7-2"></a> v2.7.2

**Release Date: October 21, 2019**

### Features

New features and changes in this release:

* <%= vars.product_full %> supports a beta <%= vars.single_leader_plan %> service plan. This plan has the
following features:
    + Replication across two routable <%= vars.app_runtime_full %> foundations secured over mTLS.
    The primary node in a foundation only trusts the secondary node in another foundation.
    + The ability to bind and push apps to a primary node in a foundation and a secondary node in another foundation.
    <%= partial '../../p-mysql/partials/mysql/multi_site_beta' %>
* Highly available (HA) cluster plans are now in general availability (GA).
* Updates Percona Server to v5.7.26-29.
* Updates pxc-release to 0.20.0.
* Updates Envoy to v1.11.1.

### Security Fix

This release includes the following security fix:

* Updates bpm-release to v1.1.3.
This update fixes Medium [CVE-2019-9893](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2019-9893).

### Resolved Issues

This release has the following fixes:

* Smoke tests no longer fail when TLS is not configured.
* You can now share MySQL for Pivotal Platform service instances across orgs and spaces using `cf share-service`.
For more information, see [Share Service Instances](./use.html#share).
* Certificate rotation now works reliably with BOSH.

